4. P. Petronii, mentioned again in 6. 45, 4, father of P. Petronius. Turpilianus, distinguished under Nero (14. 29, 1, etc.,) and of the first wife of Vitellius (H. 2. 64,1). Inscriptions (see Nipp.) show him to have been augur, cos. suff. in 772, A. D. 19, and proconsul of Asia for the unusual period of six years (Introd. vii. p. 96), · after which he was legatus of Syria under Gaius (Jos. Ant. 18. 8, 2, etc. ); in which capacity heis praised by Philo (Leg. ad Gai. 1022, folL). He was also a friend of Claudius, during whose rule he died (Sen. Lud. 14).
